[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon SageMaker, SageMaker Feature Store, AWS HealthLake, AWS Lambda, Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon QuickSight, Amazon SNS, Amazon S3 |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `sagemaker:*` (scoped to project resources), `healthlake:*`, `dynamodb:PutItem/GetItem/Query`, `s3:GetObject/PutObject`, `lambda:InvokeFunction`, `sns:Publish` |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **BAA** | Required. All services handle PHI (patient demographics, diagnoses, clinical data). |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS for training data and model artifacts. DynamoDB: encryption at rest (default). HealthLake: KMS encryption. SageMaker: KMS for training volumes and endpoints. All transit over TLS. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **VPC** | SageMaker training and endpoints in VPC. VPC endpoints for S3, DynamoDB, SageMaker Runtime, and CloudWatch Logs. HealthLake accessed via VPC endpoint. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled for all service API calls. SageMaker model lineage tracked via Model Registry. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Sample Data** | MIMIC-IV (publicly available ICU dataset) for development. Synthea for synthetic general hospital encounters. Never use real patient data in dev/test environments. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | Training: ~$5-20 per training run (ml.m5.xlarge, 1-4 hours). Inference endpoint: ~$100/month (ml.m5.large, always-on). Batch transform for daily refresh: ~$2/day. HealthLake: $0.60/10K FHIR operations. Feature Store: ~$50/month for online store. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Ingredients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Service | Role |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |------------|------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon SageMaker** | Model training, hosting, batch inference, model registry |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **SageMaker Feature Store** | Consistent feature serving for training and inference |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS HealthLake** | FHIR-compliant clinical data store; source for feature engineering |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Lambda** | Event-driven triggers for re-prediction on clinical state changes |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon DynamoDB** | Low-latency prediction store for operational queries |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon S3** | Training data, model artifacts, batch prediction outputs |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon QuickSight** | Operational dashboards for bed management and discharge planning |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon SNS** | Alerts for extended-stay predictions and discharge readiness |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS KMS** | Encryption key management for all PHI-containing stores |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon CloudWatch** | Model performance monitoring, prediction latency, drift detection |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Code
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Walkthrough
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 1: Feature extraction from clinical data.** The foundation of any LOS model is the feature set. At admission time, you extract static features (demographics, diagnosis, comorbidities, admission source). As the stay progresses, you extract dynamic features (latest labs, vital sign trends, medication changes, procedures). The feature extraction logic must handle missing data gracefully because not every patient has every lab drawn on every day. The key design decision: compute features at a consistent cadence (every 24 hours at midnight, for example) so that training data and inference data are aligned temporally. Skip this step or compute features inconsistently, and your model will learn patterns that don't exist in production.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION extract_admission_features(encounter):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Static features available at the moment of admission.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // These form the baseline prediction before any clinical trajectory is observed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     features = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "age":                  encounter.patient.age_at_admission,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "sex":                  encode_categorical(encounter.patient.sex),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "admission_source":     encode_categorical(encounter.admission_source),  // ED, direct, transfer
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "admission_type":       encode_categorical(encounter.admission_type),    // emergent, elective, urgent
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "primary_dx_category":  map_icd10_to_category(encounter.primary_diagnosis),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "drg_code":             encounter.drg_assignment,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "drg_geometric_mean":   lookup_drg_mean_los(encounter.drg_assignment),   // CMS benchmark
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "charlson_score":       compute_charlson_index(encounter.diagnosis_list),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "elixhauser_count":     count_elixhauser_categories(encounter.diagnosis_list),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "prior_admits_12mo":    count_admissions_last_12_months(encounter.patient_id),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "prior_ed_visits_12mo": count_ed_visits_last_12_months(encounter.patient_id),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "insurance_category":   encode_categorical(encounter.insurance_type),    // Medicare, Medicaid, commercial
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "day_of_week_admit":    encounter.admission_datetime.day_of_week,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "hour_of_admit":        encounter.admission_datetime.hour
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN features
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION extract_daily_features(encounter, as_of_date):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Dynamic features computed at a specific point during the stay.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // These capture the clinical trajectory and enable prediction updates.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current_day = days_between(encounter.admission_date, as_of_date)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Lab features: most recent values and trends
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     labs = get_latest_labs(encounter.patient_id, as_of_date)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     lab_features = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "wbc_latest":           labs.get("WBC", NULL),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "wbc_trend_48h":        compute_trend(labs, "WBC", hours=48),  // rising, falling, stable
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "creatinine_latest":    labs.get("CREATININE", NULL),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "albumin_latest":       labs.get("ALBUMIN", NULL),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "lactate_latest":       labs.get("LACTATE", NULL),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "abnormal_lab_count":   count_abnormal_flags(labs)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Vital sign stability
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     vitals = get_vitals_last_24h(encounter.patient_id, as_of_date)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     vital_features = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "temp_max_24h":         max(vitals.temperature),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "hr_variability_24h":   std_deviation(vitals.heart_rate),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "o2_requirement":       latest_o2_flow_rate(vitals),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "bp_stable":            is_bp_stable_24h(vitals)  // boolean
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Treatment intensity signals
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     treatment_features = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "iv_antibiotics_active":    has_active_iv_antibiotics(encounter, as_of_date),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "vasopressors_active":      has_active_vasopressors(encounter, as_of_date),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "new_consults_today":       count_consults_ordered(encounter, as_of_date),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "procedures_pending":       count_pending_procedures(encounter, as_of_date),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "diet_status":              get_diet_order_status(encounter, as_of_date)  // NPO, clear, regular
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Combine all feature sets with the current day of stay
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     all_features = merge(lab_features, vital_features, treatment_features)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     all_features["current_day_of_stay"] = current_day
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN all_features
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 2: Training data preparation.** For training, you need historical encounters with known outcomes (actual LOS). The trick is creating training examples at multiple time points during each stay. A patient who stayed 7 days generates training examples at day 0 (target: 7), day 1 (target: 6), day 2 (target: 5), and so on. This teaches the model to predict remaining LOS from any point during the stay, not just admission. Filter out encounters that ended in death or transfer (different outcome distributions) unless you're building separate models for those populations. Also exclude encounters shorter than 24 hours (observation stays) unless your use case specifically includes them.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION prepare_training_data(historical_encounters, min_los=1, max_los=60):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Build training examples from completed encounters.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Each encounter generates multiple examples: one per day of stay.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     training_examples = empty list
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR each encounter in historical_encounters:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         actual_los = encounter.actual_length_of_stay_days
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Filter: exclude very short stays (observation) and extreme outliers
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         IF actual_los < min_los OR actual_los > max_los:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             CONTINUE
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Filter: exclude deaths and transfers (build separate models for these)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         IF encounter.discharge_disposition IN ["expired", "transfer_acute"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             CONTINUE
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Generate admission-time example
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         admission_features = extract_admission_features(encounter)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         admission_features["remaining_los"] = actual_los  // target variable
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         admission_features["prediction_day"] = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         append admission_features to training_examples
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Generate daily examples for each day of the stay
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FOR day = 1 TO actual_los - 1:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             as_of_date = encounter.admission_date + day days
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             daily_features = extract_daily_features(encounter, as_of_date)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             combined = merge(admission_features, daily_features)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             combined["remaining_los"] = actual_los - day  // remaining days from this point
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             combined["prediction_day"] = day
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             append combined to training_examples
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN training_examples
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 3: Model training with service-line stratification.** One model does not fit all. Cardiac surgery patients have fundamentally different LOS drivers than general medicine patients. Train separate models per service line (or DRG family) to capture these differences. Use gradient boosted trees as the baseline because they handle the mixed feature types, missing values, and non-linear relationships well. Evaluate using mean absolute error (MAE) and the percentage of predictions within 1 day of actual. Also evaluate calibration: does the model's predicted distribution match the actual distribution?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION train_los_model(training_data, service_line):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Train a gradient boosted tree model for a specific service line.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Separate models per service line capture different LOS dynamics.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Filter training data to this service line
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     service_data = filter training_data WHERE service_line matches
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Split: 80% train, 10% validation, 10% test (time-based split, not random)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Time-based split prevents data leakage from future patterns
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     train, validation, test = temporal_split(service_data, ratios=[0.8, 0.1, 0.1])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Define features (exclude the target and metadata columns)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     feature_columns = all columns EXCEPT ["remaining_los", "encounter_id", "patient_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     target_column = "remaining_los"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Train XGBoost regressor
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model = XGBoost.train(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         objective       = "reg:squarederror",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         train_data      = train[feature_columns],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         train_labels    = train[target_column],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         validation_data = validation[feature_columns],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         validation_labels = validation[target_column],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         hyperparameters = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "max_depth":        6,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "learning_rate":    0.05,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "n_estimators":     500,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "subsample":        0.8,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "colsample_bytree": 0.8,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "early_stopping":   20,       // stop if validation doesn't improve for 20 rounds
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "min_child_weight": 10        // prevent overfitting to rare cases
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Evaluate on held-out test set
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     predictions = model.predict(test[feature_columns])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     metrics = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "mae":              mean_absolute_error(test[target_column], predictions),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "within_1_day":     percentage_within_threshold(test[target_column], predictions, threshold=1),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "within_2_days":    percentage_within_threshold(test[target_column], predictions, threshold=2),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "median_error":     median(absolute(test[target_column] - predictions)),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "r_squared":        r2_score(test[target_column], predictions)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Log metrics and register model
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     log_metrics(metrics, service_line=service_line)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     register_model(model, service_line=service_line, metrics=metrics)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN model, metrics
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 4: Real-time inference for current inpatients.** For operational use, the system needs to produce updated predictions for all current inpatients at least daily, and ideally whenever significant clinical events occur (new lab results, procedure completion, status change). The inference pipeline pulls the latest features from the feature store, selects the appropriate service-line model, runs prediction, and writes the result to the prediction store. Include a confidence interval (not just a point estimate) so that operations teams can distinguish between "we're fairly sure this patient leaves tomorrow" and "this could be anywhere from 2 to 10 more days."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION predict_remaining_los(encounter_id):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Generate an updated LOS prediction for a current inpatient.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Called on a schedule (daily) and on clinical event triggers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Get encounter metadata to select the right model
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     encounter = get_active_encounter(encounter_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     service_line = encounter.service_line
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Pull latest features from the feature store (ensures consistency with training)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     admission_features = feature_store.get_online(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         feature_group = "admission_features",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         record_id     = encounter_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     daily_features = feature_store.get_online(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         feature_group = "daily_features",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         record_id     = encounter_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Combine feature sets
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     features = merge(admission_features, daily_features)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Select the model for this service line
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model_endpoint = get_model_endpoint(service_line)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Run inference
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     prediction = invoke_endpoint(model_endpoint, features)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Compute confidence interval using quantile predictions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // (requires training quantile regression models or using prediction intervals)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     lower_bound = max(0, prediction.point_estimate - prediction.uncertainty)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     upper_bound = prediction.point_estimate + prediction.uncertainty
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Calculate predicted discharge date
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current_day = days_since_admission(encounter)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     predicted_discharge = encounter.admission_date + current_day + prediction.point_estimate
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Store prediction
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "encounter_id":         encounter_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patient_id":           encounter.patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "unit":                 encounter.current_unit,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "bed":                  encounter.current_bed,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "service_line":         service_line,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "current_day_of_stay":  current_day,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "predicted_remaining":  round(prediction.point_estimate, 1),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "confidence_lower":     round(lower_bound, 1),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "confidence_upper":     round(upper_bound, 1),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "predicted_discharge":  predicted_discharge,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "drg_expected_los":     lookup_drg_mean_los(encounter.drg_assignment),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "exceeds_expected":     (current_day + prediction.point_estimate) > lookup_drg_mean_los(encounter.drg_assignment),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "prediction_timestamp": current_utc_timestamp(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "model_version":        model_endpoint.version
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write_to_prediction_store(result)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Alert if predicted to significantly exceed DRG expected LOS
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF result.exceeds_expected AND current_day <= 2:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         send_alert("extended_stay_early_warning", result)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN result
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 5: Daily batch refresh and monitoring.** Once a day, re-score all current inpatients and compare yesterday's predictions against today's reality. Patients who were discharged yesterday provide ground truth for model monitoring. Track prediction accuracy over time and trigger retraining when performance degrades. Also monitor for distribution drift: if the patient population is changing (new service lines, seasonal patterns, pandemic surges), the model may need updating even if recent accuracy looks acceptable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION daily_batch_refresh():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Run every morning: update all predictions and monitor model performance.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // 1. Score all current inpatients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     active_encounters = get_all_active_inpatient_encounters()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR each encounter in active_encounters:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Update features in the feature store
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         daily_features = extract_daily_features(encounter, today)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         feature_store.put_online("daily_features", encounter.encounter_id, daily_features)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Generate fresh prediction
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         predict_remaining_los(encounter.encounter_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // 2. Evaluate yesterday's predictions against actual outcomes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     discharged_yesterday = get_encounters_discharged(yesterday)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     errors = empty list
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR each encounter in discharged_yesterday:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Get the prediction that was active at the start of yesterday
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         yesterday_prediction = get_prediction_as_of(encounter.encounter_id, yesterday)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         actual_remaining = days_between(yesterday, encounter.discharge_datetime)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         error = yesterday_prediction.predicted_remaining - actual_remaining
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         append error to errors
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // 3. Compute and log monitoring metrics
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     monitoring_metrics = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "date":                 today,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patients_scored":      length(active_encounters),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patients_discharged":  length(discharged_yesterday),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "mae_yesterday":        mean(absolute(errors)),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "bias_yesterday":       mean(errors),  // positive = overpredicting LOS
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "within_1_day_pct":     percentage_within(errors, threshold=1),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "active_census":        length(active_encounters)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     log_monitoring_metrics(monitoring_metrics)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // 4. Alert if model performance is degrading
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF monitoring_metrics.mae_yesterday > PERFORMANCE_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         send_alert("model_performance_degradation", monitoring_metrics)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN monitoring_metrics
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
